<subSubSection id="EF1D0272CAB4528D2D471C2E5133030E" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="26593032051B35609777CA300789D82E" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECF9C7DDC94FA680FBB606CA46404F1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="812502C79699CE99AD246D330224D416" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Female.</emphasis>
Head and mesosoma dark metallic green; gaster brown with or without yellowish patch near base. Antennae with funicle dark brown, scape and pedicel pale yellow or with dark on dorsal surface, clava white. Legs yellow with coxae and trochanters white. Mesoscutellum longitudinally sculptured. Metascutellum raised-reticulate. Propodeum shorter than mesoscutellum, with median carina and plicae complete. POL 1.6-1.7 
<normalizedToken id="3E1E1B281550422585DB1E3B7C397919" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOL. Malar sulcus present, malar space 0.4-0.5 
<normalizedToken id="3462A4A1F9037F4696A67633D8CBC163" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye height. Antennae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="329D329961B3502C03C77082F6735DA1" captionStart="Figures 16–20" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 20. Hemiptarsenus jilinus Tao, female 16 habitus in lateral view 17 habitus in dorsal view 18 antenna 19 fore wing 20 mesosoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.85228.figures16-20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688638" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">18</figureCitation>
) with scape slender and cylindrical, 6.7-8.2 
<normalizedToken id="EE5469BECAE91E0146F3A25C17E10CBB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, extending far beyond vertex; pedicel 1.6-1.8 
<normalizedToken id="BB78000A0A28D2383C5A7C96A83FE2C6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide; funicle 4-segmented, F1 2.9-3.7 
<normalizedToken id="054E4E10207C2EA0EC7B3E225FA43C16" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, F2 3.4-4.1 
<normalizedToken id="305B8E1982EC82821F1A5A60A7CB6830" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, F3 and F4 2.3-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="EF0AE1D3F75FF2B30554861A52F8A732" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
and 2.2-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="2B263630534C2D3D5C362BAF27120CCB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide respectively; clava 2-segmented, 2.4-2.6 
<normalizedToken id="C7D52AE08716C57AC25484A5615E9461" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Fore wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B98506AD5A33046D8BF5B44463B0820B" captionStart="Figures 16–20" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 20. Hemiptarsenus jilinus Tao, female 16 habitus in lateral view 17 habitus in dorsal view 18 antenna 19 fore wing 20 mesosoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.85228.figures16-20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688638" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">19</figureCitation>
) 2.6-2.8 
<normalizedToken id="0360ED16F0EA7CAB013D5184D051A882" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Costal cell 13.3-13.7 
<normalizedToken id="2D3F7998C10F793E8CE9B100A421C20B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Speculum present, closed posteriorly. MV 1.1-1.3 
<normalizedToken id="BA16863DB10BB55CE469E7CCC1F92DA0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
